    <p>When a client is not satisfied with the services provided by our company, we welcome the opportunity to hear about it. Every complaint is accepted and treated with care, and we will always use our best endeavours to resolve the matter and to improve the quality of our services to the highest possible standard.</p>
    <p>Resolution of a complaint follows two stages: an internal procedure and, where necessary, a government procedure. Clients are asked to work through the internal procedure first. If the internal procedure does not resolve the complaint to the client's satisfaction, the client has the right to proceed to the government procedure, as set out below.</p>

    <h2 class="section">1. Internal Procedure</h2>
    <p>If a client is not satisfied with any service provided by the licensed immigration adviser or by our company, was not treated well, believes the adviser breached the Code of Conduct or any New Zealand law, believes an application was unsuccessful due to adviser error, or has any other unresolved concern, the complaint should be raised with our licensed immigration adviser, Hendry Dai, using the details below. Please describe what happened, clearly explain the problem, and state the outcome you are seeking.</p>
